The paper discusses recent computer vision techniques used in the assessment of image aesthetic quality, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep learning techniques also suggests the machine learning (cs.MM) and the machine learning sub-category (cs.LG). The evaluation criteria and metrics used in the paper suggest the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the focus on visual aesthetics and photographic rules suggests the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
